Create a table-instance from an open-data dataset

Source: R/od_table.R
od_table_class.Rd

R6 Class open data datasets.

Super class

STATcubeR::sc_data -> od_table

Active bindings

json

parsed version of https://data.statistik.gv.at/ogd/json?dataset=${id}

header

parsed version of https://data.statistik.gv.at/data/${id}_HEADER.csv.Similar contents can be found in $meta.

language

language to be used for labeling. "en" or "de"

resources

lists all files downloaded from the server to contruct this table

Methods

Public methods

  • od_table_class$new()

Inherited methods

  • STATcubeR::sc_data$field()

  • STATcubeR::sc_data$tabulate()

  • STATcubeR::sc_data$total_codes()

Method new()

This class is not exported. Use od_table() to initialize objects of class od_table.

Usage

od_table_class$new(id, language = c("en", "de"))

Arguments

id

the id of the data-set that should be accessed

language

language to be used for labeling. "en" or "de"
